name: Great Lasik Consultation
about: All laser vision correction consultations involve a thorough eye exam, during which your eye health and vision will be evaluated. A series of diagnostic tests will be performed to look at every aspect of your eyes.

name: Free Lense Consultation
about: Lens replacement surgery is a permanent answer to vision problems such as presbyopia (the gradual loss of your eyes' ability to focus on nearby objects), astigmatism (near vision and blurred distance) and cataracts, as well as long-sightedness (hyperopia) and short-sightedness (myopia).

name: Eye Infection Care
about: An eye infection can happen when bacteria, viruses or fungi invade part of the eye or its surrounding area. This includes the clear front surface of the eye (cornea) and the thin, moist membrane lining the outer eye and inner eyelids (conjunctiva). Many eye infections go away on their own or with simple treatment.

name: Dry Infection Threat
about: Bacterial infections are treated with antibiotics such as amoxicillin, erythromycin and ciprofloxacin. There are many different types of antibiotic, with different ways of working; the choice depends on the type of infection you have. Fungi commonly cause skin infections such as athlete's foot and ringworm.
